      },
      "date": "2018-10-09 19:42:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> (2 comments)\n > \n > It would be good to have a basic test that verifies these values\n > could actually be set, maybe as a new test in the lnet-selftest\n > script?\n\nNow that LUTF is being worked upon to be build along with lustre. I am thinking, I will push a patch under the same ticket to add the test-script to LUTF which test this functionality. \nSince LUTF is on multi-rail branch, so that patch will go to multi-rail branch.\nOpinion?",
